<div class="adv-richtext" data-cs-capture>
  {{ section.settings.intro_text }}
</div>

{% if section.settings.inside_outside_image != blank %}
  <div class="adv-image">
    {{
      section.settings.inside_outside_image
      | image_url: width: 1280
      | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: section.settings.inside_outside_image.alt, data-cs-mask: 'false'
    }}
  </div>
{% endif %}

<p class="adv-subhead" data-cs-capture>{{ section.settings.subhead }}</p>

<div class="adv-richtext" data-cs-capture>
  {{ section.settings.body_quality }}
</div>

{% if section.settings.color_comparison_image != blank %}
  <div class="adv-image">
    {{
      section.settings.color_comparison_image
      | image_url: width: 1280
      | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: section.settings.color_comparison_image.alt, data-cs-mask: 'false'
    }}
  </div>
{% endif %}

<div class="adv-richtext" data-cs-capture>
  {{ section.settings.body_process }}
</div>

{% if section.settings.process_image != blank %}
  <div class="adv-image">
    {{
      section.settings.process_image
      | image_url: width: 1280
      | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: section.settings.process_image.alt, data-cs-mask: 'false'
    }}
  </div>
{% endif %}

<div class="adv-section-break"></div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Advertorial Quality Proof",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "intro_text",
      "label": "Intro Text (for scrollers)",
      "default": "<p>If you're still reading, you probably want to understand exactly why quality matters so much with moringa — and how to tell the difference between the real thing and the cheap alternatives that give the plant a bad name.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "inside_outside_image",
      "label": "Inside / Outside Illustration"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "subhead",
      "label": "Section Heading",
      "default": "How to tell real moringa from the brown powder that doesn't work."
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "body_quality",
      "label": "Quality Comparison Text",
      "default": "<p>Walk into any health store and you'll find moringa powder for Rp 50,000. It's brown. It's bitter. Most of it is ground-up stems.</p><p>Most brands shred the entire branch — leaves, stems, bark — because it's faster and cheaper. The result is a powder that's oxidized before it reaches you. Low absorption. Low potency. That's why so many women try moringa once and give up.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "color_comparison_image",
      "label": "Green vs Brown Comparison Image"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "body_process",
      "label": "Process / Provenance Text",
      "default": "<p>Leaf-only moringa looks different. Vibrant green, like matcha. The difference comes down to whether the stems were removed — by hand, one leaf at a time.</p><p>This process takes one full hour to produce just 12 grams of powder. Treelogy follows this method for every batch. Harvested at dawn in Karangasem, Bali. Hand-separated. Dehydrated at 38°C for 22 hours to protect heat-sensitive vitamins and enzymes. No shortcuts.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "process_image",
      "label": "Farm / Process Image"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
